summary: Steve, looking back and counting the members of the squad™: Hold up, I think we lost Loki in the crowd. Tony, deadpan, sipping...
body:
Steve, looking back and counting the members of the squad™: Hold up, I think we lost Loki in the crowd.

Tony, deadpan, sipping his coffee: Oh good! It’s about time.

Peter, worried: Oh no! We’ve gotta find him! *prepares himself to web up to a roof to scan the area*

Thor, resting a hand on Peter’s shoulder to stop him: It’s alright, young one. I’ll take care of this.

Thor, cupping his hands around his mouth: LOKI IS WORTHY OF LOVE AND REDEMPTION

Loki, dropping whatever he was messing with to burst out of the crowd: NO THE FUCK I’M NOT

Thor, grinning: There he is

summary: Cut the Wires Sequence Three: Hope for My Sake You know
title: Cut the Wires Sequence Three: Hope for My Sake You know
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2Dm86zd

by Taste_is_Sweet

This time Steve didn’t run towards the threat while he was effectively blinded. A human mercenary was simple, but one swipe of the giant robot suit’s arm might kill him. He waited for Tony to use his repulsors and take the suit out. Only Tony didn’t.

Tony was still hovering, hands raised to fire. He looked untouched. Only he wasn’t doing anything. It was like he’d frozen—

He had frozen, Steve realized. Of course he had.

title: all that i wanted
body:
The curve of the earth tells me some things they won’t be changing


The North Star, the dipper, the oceans and deserts


But over my shoulder everything’s ashes and ruin


Stretched out before me is shadows and broken white lines

The curve of your neck and the kisses you gave in the morning
The sound of my name leaving your mouth
All of it gone now, blowing like dust on the highway
Time may erase me, but one thing will remain

All that I wanted was you
